# ── Backend API URL (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# In the single-service Render deployment, the frontend and backend share the
# same origin and all API calls use relative paths. VITE_API_URL is NOT needed.
#
# Only set this if you need to point a locally-running frontend at a remote
# backend (e.g. staging environment), or if running frontend and backend as
# separate services.
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT — copy this file to .env and keep the default:
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
#
# LOCAL DEV (single-service simulation — Vite proxy handles this automatically):
# Leave VITE_API_URL unset. The vite.config.js proxy forwards /auth, /codes,
# /history, /execute to localhost:8000 transparently.
